Build succeeds. Here's the summary:

**`[ExpectedException]` → `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`**

```csharp
// Before (MSTest v3)
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest() { DoWork(null); }

// After (MSTest v4)
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest() {
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => DoWork(null));
}
```

`ThrowsExactly` is also better practice — it catches the exception inline so you can inspect it (e.g., check the message), and it fails immediately at the right call site rather than anywhere in the method. For async methods, use `Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>()`.
